<div type="definition">

    <p resp="#CH" modified="2021-03-18T18:08:51.636+09:00">UNTRUE so that MANY are NOT ABLE to IMAGINE IT to be TRUE.  </p>
        <div type="definition" resp="#CH" modified="2022-07-20T18:57:39.529+09:00">
            <p>CLEARly UNTRUE so that MANY are NOT ABLE to IMAGINE IT to be TRUE.</p>
        </div>
        <div type="definition" resp="#CH" modified="2023-09-13T01:16:18.724+09:00">
            <p>CLEARLY UNTRUE AND STRANGE. </p>
        </div>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The current word for contradictory absurdity is bèi 悖.</p>
<p>2. Huāng 荒 focusses on the confusion more than the contradictoriness.</p>
<p>3. Dàn 誕 focusses on the loquaciousness of absurd discourse.</p>
<p>4. Guāi miù 乖謬 focusses on the misguidedness which is the result of incoherence.</p>
        </div>
